  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in Senate",
    "asOf": "2026-05-14",
    "date": "2026-05-18T15:07:07Z",
    "text": "This bill authorizes the Capitol Police Board to increase the mandatory retirement age for a member of the Capitol Police to up to age 62. Under current law, members of the Capitol Police are generally subject to mandatory retirement at age 57 (with some exceptions), but\u00a0may receive a\u00a0waiver from the board\u00a0authorizing them to continue working until they are 60."
  },
